  32:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ltdc.c **** 
  33:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ltdc.c ****      (#) Initialize the LTDC low level resources by implementing the HAL_LTDC_MspInit() API:
  34:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ltdc.c ****          (##) Enable the LTDC interface clock
  35:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ltdc.c ****          (##) NVIC configuration if you need to use interrupt process
  36:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ltdc.c ****              (+++) Configure the LTDC interrupt priority
  37:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ltdc.c ****              (+++) Enable the NVIC LTDC IRQ Channel
  38:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ltdc.c **** 
  39:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ltdc.c ****      (#) Initialize the required configuration through the following parameters:
  40:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ltdc.c ****          the LTDC timing, the horizontal and vertical polarity, the pixel clock polarity,
  41:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ltdc.c ****          Data Enable polarity and the LTDC background color value using HAL_LTDC_Init() function
  42:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ltdc.c **** 
  43:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ltdc.c ****      *** Configuration ***
  44:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ltdc.c ****      =========================
  45:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ltdc.c ****      [..]
  46:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ltdc.c ****      (#) Program the required configuration through the following parameters:
  47:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ltdc.c ****          the pixel format, the blending factors, input alpha value, the window size
  48:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ltdc.c ****          and the image size using HAL_LTDC_ConfigLayer() function for foreground
  49:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ltdc.c ****          or/and background layer.
  50:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ltdc.c **** 
  51:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ltdc.c ****      (#) Optionally, configure and enable the CLUT using HAL_LTDC_ConfigCLUT() and
  52:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ltdc.c ****          HAL_LTDC_EnableCLUT functions.
  53:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ltdc.c **** 
  54:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ltdc.c ****      (#) Optionally, enable the Dither using HAL_LTDC_EnableDither().
  55:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ltdc.c **** 
  56:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ltdc.c ****      (#) Optionally, configure and enable the Color keying using HAL_LTDC_ConfigColorKeying()
  57:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ltdc.c ****          and HAL_LTDC_EnableColorKeying functions.
  58:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ltdc.c **** 
  59:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ltdc.c ****      (#) Optionally, configure LineInterrupt using HAL_LTDC_ProgramLineEvent()
  60:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ltdc.c ****          function
  61:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ltdc.c **** 
  62:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ltdc.c ****      (#) If needed, reconfigure and change the pixel format value, the alpha value
  63:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ltdc.c ****          value, the window size, the window position and the layer start address
  64:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ltdc.c ****          for foreground or/and background layer using respectively the following
  65:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ltdc.c ****          functions: HAL_LTDC_SetPixelFormat(), HAL_LTDC_SetAlpha(), HAL_LTDC_SetWindowSize(),
  66:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ltdc.c ****          HAL_LTDC_SetWindowPosition() and HAL_LTDC_SetAddress().
  67:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ltdc.c **** 
  68:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ltdc.c ****      (#) Variant functions with _NoReload suffix allows to set the LTDC configuration/settings with
  69:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ltdc.c ****          This is useful in case when the program requires to modify serval LTDC settings (on one or
  70:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ltdc.c ****          then applying(reload) these settings in one shot by calling the function HAL_LTDC_Reload()
  71:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ltdc.c **** 
  72:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ltdc.c ****          After calling the _NoReload functions to set different color/format/layer settings,
  73:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ltdc.c ****          the program shall call the function HAL_LTDC_Reload() to apply(reload) these settings.
  74:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ltdc.c ****          Function HAL_LTDC_Reload() can be called with the parameter ReloadType set to LTDC_RELOAD_
  75:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ltdc.c ****          an immediate reload is required.
  76:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ltdc.c ****          Function HAL_LTDC_Reload() can be called with the parameter ReloadType set to LTDC_RELOAD_
  77:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ltdc.c ****          the reload should be done in the next vertical blanking period,
  78:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ltdc.c ****          this option allows to avoid display flicker by applying the new settings during the vertic
  79:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ltdc.c **** 
  80:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ltdc.c **** 
  81:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ltdc.c ****      (#) To control LTDC state you can use the following function: HAL_LTDC_GetState()
  82:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ltdc.c **** 
  83:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ltdc.c ****      *** LTDC HAL driver macros list ***
  84:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ltdc.c ****      =============================================
  85:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ltdc.c ****      [..]
  86:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ltdc.c ****        Below the list of most used macros in LTDC HAL driver.
  87:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ltdc.c **** 
  88:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ltdc.c ****       (+) __HAL_LTDC_ENABLE: Enable the LTDC.
ARM GAS  C:\Users\28576\AppData\Local\Temp\ccWmjvvp.s 			page 3


  89:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ltdc.c ****       (+) __HAL_LTDC_DISABLE: Disable the LTDC.
  90:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ltdc.c ****       (+) __HAL_LTDC_LAYER_ENABLE: Enable an LTDC Layer.
  91:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ltdc.c ****       (+) __HAL_LTDC_LAYER_DISABLE: Disable an LTDC Layer.
  92:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ltdc.c ****       (+) __HAL_LTDC_RELOAD_IMMEDIATE_CONFIG: Reload  Layer Configuration.
  93:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ltdc.c ****       (+) __HAL_LTDC_GET_FLAG: Get the LTDC pending flags.
  94:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ltdc.c ****       (+) __HAL_LTDC_CLEAR_FLAG: Clear the LTDC pending flags.
  95:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ltdc.c ****       (+) __HAL_LTDC_ENABLE_IT: Enable the specified LTDC interrupts.
  96:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ltdc.c ****       (+) __HAL_LTDC_DISABLE_IT: Disable the specified LTDC interrupts.
  97:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ltdc.c ****       (+) __HAL_LTDC_GET_IT_SOURCE: Check whether the specified LTDC interrupt has occurred or not.
